} 9. Nd4 $1 {with a clear advantage to White.}) (8... a6 9. Bxc6+ bxc6 10. fxe5
fxe5 11. Nxe5 $1 {
(never forget this trick, our copyright cheapo in this chapter)} Bxe5 12. Qh5+
Bf7 13. Rxf7 $1 Bxh2+ 14. Qxh2 $1 {and now:} -- (14... Qxf7 {is met by} 15.
Qe5+ Kd7 (15... Qe7 $4 {loses to} 16. Nxd5 $1) ({, while} 15... Ne7 $4 16. Rf1
{shows the difference between recapturing on h2 with the queen: White's rook
ejects a key defender of e7, and} Qg6 17. Ba3 {wins}) 16. Na4 Nf6 17. Nc5+ Kc8
